text:
Blk 145 Coffeeshop on the side nearer to the wet market there is a nameless rojak stall hidden behind the coffeeshop drink stall. An old grandma with very short white hair is operating it.

I had zero expectations since it was a nameless shop.  I had a very simple looking plate of rojak but I was wrong.  This must be one of the best tasting rojak I had in the area!  The additional asam sauce in the rojak, that sourness really clears down your palate after a heavy meal.  Ingredients are very fresh! The youtiao and cuttlefish are freshly grilled for you totally delicious.  Very good as a filler dessert especially if you are still not full after a meal.  Very refreshing.  You can have the same ingredients for rojak everywhere but to make good rojak need skills. Grandma got skills :D A hidden gem indeed.

Classic old school "shopping mall". Like back to the past. Unfortunately for now still packed with residents though it's Covid period. Otherwise love this place .... Only thing ...hardly can find seats to makan
A very convenient place at the heart of the neighbourhood where one can find most of the basic necessities.
